					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's patently obvious that you just found a neat photo and ran with it—but that's not a bad thing. If anything, it makes me slightly nostalgic for the days when that was how 90% of articles came about.</p> <p>But that's neither here nor there. I thought that the use of asterisks to denote actions felt really off-tone, but the twist at the end and the emotional weight behind it were effective enough for me to leave feeling happy I'd read this. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
