					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5913421#post-3797645</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5913421/scp-3907#post-3797645</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 12 May 2018 00:02:51 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Drjemin</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3625466</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Hm&#8230; not bad. Aside from a few clinical tone slip-ups (i.e. &quot;being in incredible, practically mint condition for its age&quot; might work better as &quot;being in atypically pristine condition for its age&quot;), it's okay. The addendum is nicely written, with solid, believable dialogue.</p> <p>You might like to use this image code instead:</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[include&#32;component:image-block</span> name=THE NAME OF YOUR IMAGE FILE|<br /> <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;caption=THE&#32;TEXT&#32;YOU&#32;WANT&#32;SHOWN&#32;UNDERNEATH&#32;YOUR&#32;IMAGE</span> ]]</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>The one you're using now is kind of antiquated.</p> <p>Also, I noticed a small issue with the verb tenses at the very end of your addendum.</p> <blockquote> <p>SCP-3907-1 and SCP-3907-3 through -5 stand and raise their glasses.</p> </blockquote> <blockquote> <p>SCP-3907-6 jumped over the table as the entities finished the toast. SCP-3907 returned to its inactive state.</p> </blockquote> <p>First is present tense, second is past tense. I'd recommend making them both the same as the writing feels kind of disjointed otherwise.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
